[1] Cholera - Angola (Country-wide, Cuando Cubango province)
Date: Tue 25 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News24 [edited]
<http://www.news24.com/News24/Africa/News/0,,2-11-1447_1972771,00.html>

Cholera in Angola had spread to a 15th province, as the death toll
reached 2089, and the number of cases exceeded 50 000, said the WHO
on Mon 24 Jul 2006.
WHO reported that "the southern province of Cuando Cubango confirmed
cholera cases on 19 Jul 2006. Up to now, there were 48 cumulative
cases and 6 deaths."
The WHO also reported that from 13 Feb to 23 Jul 2006, "a total of 50
768 cumulative cases and 2089 deaths have been reported in 15 out of
the 18 provinces" in Angola. It added that 62 new cases and 2 deaths
had been reported in the previous 24 hours alone.
The highest toll since February 2006 was recorded in the eastern
coastal province of Benguela, with 517 deaths, followed by 302
fatalities in Luanda and 244 in the Malange region.
The deadly but easily treatable water-borne disease broke out
initially in Luanda's northern slum of Boa Vista and rapidly spread
throughout the seaside capital and to other parts of the oil-rich
southern African country.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
The location of Cuando Cubango province in the southeast corner of
the country can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>.
The 3 provinces yet to be reported involved are Cunene, Moxico and
Lunda Sul. They also can be found on the map. - Mod.LL]
