[2] Cholera - Sudan
Date: Mon 24 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: WHO [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/EGUA-6S2RDV?OpenDocument>

As of 23 Jul 2006, the total number of cholera cases in Sudan is
4991, with 165 deaths and a case fatality rate of 3.3 percent. The
highest number of cholera cases have been found in North Kordofan,
with 1383 and 43 deaths and a case fatality rate of 3.1 percent and
in Khartoum with 924 cases and 41 deaths and a case fatality rate of
4.4 percent.
State / Cases on 22 Jul 2006 / Deaths / Cumulative Cases / Deaths / CFR
Khartoum / 2 / 0 / 924 / 41 / 4.4
N. Kordofan / 2 / 0 / 1383 / 43 / 3.1
White Nile / 0 / 0 / 675 / 13 / 1.9
South Darfur / - / - / 440 / 12 / 2.7
S. Kordofan / - / - / 395 / 13 / 3.3
River Nile / 11 / 0 / 526 / 14 / 2.7
Kassala / 3 / 0 / 216 / 13 / 6.0
Al Gazira / 0 / 0 / 79 / 5 / 6.3
Gadarif / 5 / 0 / 250 / 5 / 2.0
Other states / 3 / 0 / 103 / 6 / 5.8
Total / 26 / 0 / 4991 / 165 / 3.3
