[3] Diarrhea - Tanzania (Zanzibar)
Date: Fri 28 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Pravda [edited]
<http://english.pravda.ru/news/world/28-07-2006/83628-Zanzibar-0>

In Zanzibar, 300 children have been hospitalized in July 2006 after
drinking dirty water. The children, between the ages of 6 months and
2 years, suffered from severe diarrhea, said Dr. Fatma Aboud of Mnazi
Mmoja Hospital. The facility was forced to put as many as 3 children
in one bed because of the outbreak, she said.
"The illnesses are not life-threatening, but we call upon parents to
boil water before drinking it and to keep their environments clean,"
Aboud said.
Zanzibar, a semiautonomous part of Tanzania, has a persistent water
shortage. In many parts of this impoverished nation, residents rely
on leaking pipes or ponds for drinking water.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
