[4] Cholera - Nepal (Kavre Palanchok)
Date: Tue 25 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Rising Nepal [edited]
<http://www.gorkhapatra.org.np/content.php?nid=4914>

Four people have been found suffering from cholera in various parts
of Kavre district, including Sanga, Panauti and Kavre, Chief of the
District Public Health Office Ganga Raj Aryal said. While undergoing
check-up at the Dhulikhel Hospital, _Vibrio cholerae_ were found in
the 4 people reported between ages 33 and 63 years old.
Additionally, of the 28 gastroenteritis patients in Chalal
Ganeshsthan of Kavre, 4 are suspected to be suffering from cholera.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Nepal showing the Kavre Palanchok district in the Bagmati
zone of the Central Region can be found at
<http://ncthakur.itgo.com/map04.htm>. - Mod.LL]
